                ],
                "institute": "3CPRNPC"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " PD-300 neutron generator"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "About 10 gram of Dy2O3 (99.995% purity) powder was",
                " pressed at 980 MPa, and thin 20 mm diameter samples",
                " were obtained.",
                "The samples were irradiated in contact with the target,",
                " sandwiched between standard Nb foils (99.999% purity,",
                " 0.5 mm thick) of the same diameter utilized to",
                " monitor the neutron fluence via the 93Nb(n,2n)92mNb",
                " reaction.",
                "The groups of samples were placed at 0 deg or 135 deg",
                " relative to the beam direction and were centered about",
                " the tritium-titanium (T-Ti) target at distances of",
                " about 40 mm."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "D-T"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " A T-Ti target was used in the generator, with a",
                " thickness of 2.40 mg/cm2, and the diameter of the",
                " active zone was 12 mm. Neutrons were produced with an",
                " effective deuteron beam energy of 134 keV and beam",
                " current of 260 uA."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The gamma ray activities of 162Tb, 163Tb and",
                " 93mNb were determined by a high-purity germanium",
                " detector (ORTEC, model GEM 60P, crystal diameter:",
                " 70.1 mm, crystal length: 72.3 mm) with a relative",
                " efficiency of about 68% and an energy resolution of",
                " 1.69 keV at 1.332 MeV for 60Co.",
                "The efficiency of the detector was measured using",
                " various standard gamma sources, namely Co-57, Co-60,",
                " Cd-109, Ba-133, Cs-137, Eu-152, Am-241 and Ra-226.",
                "Standard Reference Material QCR9110 was obtained from",
                " China Institute of Atomic Energy (CIAE), scope of",
                " activity is 3.04E4 to 4.26E4 Bq."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SIBAR"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " An Au-Si surface barrier detector was located",
                " at 135 degree to accompany the a-particle tube placed",
                " at a distance of 1.10 m from the target."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Irradiation of the samples was lasted about",
                " 60 min with a yield about 3 to 4E10 n/(4pi*s)."
              ]
            }
          ],
